    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Power Relay Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Power Relay Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the relay. The inspection method is the same for each relay. No continuity between No. 1 and No. 2 terminals. There should be continuity between No.3 and No.4 terminals."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When inspecting diode-type relays, apply the battery voltage backwards, as this may damage the diodes in the relay."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "There should be continuity between No.1 and No.2 terminals when battery voltage is applied between No.3 and No.4 terminals."
    },
